        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 1:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 138 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Hog Mountain, or 8
miles northeast of Lawrenceville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lawrenceville, Winder, Jefferson, Buford, Braselton, Auburn, Dacula,
Arcade, Hoschton, Pendergrass, Carl, Talmo, Fort Yargo State Park,
County Line, Thompsons Mill, Harbin, Chateau Elan, Russell, Road
Atlanta-Lanier Speedway, and Hog Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
